        "# Setting up IDL Notebooks in VS Code",
        "",
        "## Linking IDL to Run in Notebooks",
        "",
        "### 1. Download and License IDL",
        "",
        "If you have not already, instructions on how to download IDL can be found here:  ",
        "[IDL Installation Guide](https://www.nv5geospatialsoftware.com/docs/idl-install.html)  ",
        "_Remember the location where you downloaded it._",
        "",
        "---",
        "",
        "### 2. Locate and Open IDL for VSCode's Extension Settings",
        "",
        "**Option 1**:",
        "",
        "- Locate the **IDL for VSCode** extension  ",
        "  <img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/interactive-data-language/vscode-idl/refs/heads/main/extension/images/idlicon.svg\" width=\"30\" >",
        "  in your **Activity Bar** to the left and open it.",
        "- Then, select **Open Extension Settings** from the **Quick Access** menu.",
        "",
        "**Option 2**:",
        "",
        "- Open the **Settings** menu by pressing `Ctrl+,` or `Cmd+,`.",
        "- Search for `idl.IDL.directory` directly in the Settings search bar.",
        "",
        "---",
        "",
        "### 3. Link IDL to the IDL for VSCode Extension",
        "",
        "- In the Settings, navigate to the **`idl.IDL:directory`** field.",
        "- Enter the path to the **bin** directory **containing** the `idl.exe`.",
        "",
        "  _For example:_  ",
        "  `\"C:\\Program Files\\<User>\\IDLXX\\bin\\bin.x86_64\"`",
        "",
        "---",
        ""
